Date and Time Functions in Excel
DATE: Used to create a date with the specified year, month, and day.

Syntax: =DATE(year, month, day)
DAY: Returns the day of the month from a given date.

Syntax: =DAY(cell_name)
EDATE: Returns a date that is a specified number of months before or after a start date.

Syntax: =EDATE(starting_date, number_of_months)

Note: Excel stores dates as serial numbers, so you may need to format the cell as a date to display it correctly.

WEEKDAY: Returns the day of the week for a given date.

Syntax: =WEEKDAY(cell_name)
HOUR: Extracts the hour from a time value.

Syntax: =HOUR(cell_name)
MINUTE: Extracts the minute from a time value.

Syntax: =MINUTE(cell_name)
